Date: Sat 19 Feb 2000
From: Dick Hamilton <rihamilto@home.com>
Source: EPPO Reporting Service 2000, No. 02

2000/035 More findings of _Xanthomonas axonopodis_ pv. _citri_ in Florida (US)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
In Florida (US), Xanthomonas axonopodis pv. citri (EPPO A1 quarantine pest)
was recently found in Sun City Center (Tampa Bay, Hillsborough county). The
site is a row of citrus trees near private houses. In addition, it is also
reported that citrus canker has reached 10 commercial citrus orchards in
the Miami-Dade county.
Pest Alert posting, University of Florida,1999-12-06. Citrus canker found
near Tampa Bay. <http://extlab7.entnem.ufl.edu/PestAlert/>
